      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey so my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning kinda yellow and pale compared to the top ones. what's probably going on with them?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It sounds like your tomato plants may be experiencing a problem called \"lower leaf chlorosis.\" This can happen when the roots are not getting enough nutrients, particularly iron. You might consider checking the soil pH, as a too acidic or too alkaline environment can inhibit nutrient uptake. Also, ensure your plants have enough water but not too much, as overwatering can cause root issues. If the problem persists, you might need to apply a balanced fertilizer or iron chelate to help your plants out. Remember, every plant is unique, so keep an eye on them and adjust care as needed.",
