    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If your soil is too acidic, you'll want to add lime to raise the pH level. Lime is a common soil amendment that can help neutralize acidity. It's important to test your soil first to determine the current pH level and the amount of lime you'll need. Add lime gradually, as over-liming can cause other problems. Once you've added lime, water it in well and test the pH again after a few weeks to see if further adjustments are needed. Keep in mind that tomatoes prefer a slightly acidic to neutral pH, so aim for a range of 6.0 to 6.8. Remember, it's always best to err on the side of caution and consult a local cooperative extension service for precise recommendations for your area.",
